en]][[File:SS Kaiser Wilhelm der Gro\u00dfe.png|center|thumb]]<br />\n|10 June 1903\n[[Ellis Island|New York]]\n|[https://www.familysearch.org/tree/person/details/M7GB-CZW Paty - Anezka (1882-1960)] [to meet unknown A Havlik]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:JFRN-929|title=New York Passenger Arrival Lists (Ellis Island), 1892-1924|last=Paty|first=|date=1903|website=FamilySearch|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n|12 January 1904\n[[SS Kaiser Wilhelm II]]\n\n[[Bremen]][[File:Kaiser wilhelm 2.jpg|center|thumb|172x172px]]\n|20 January 1904\n[[Ellis Island|New York]]\n|[https://www.familysearch.org/tree/person/details/LHFC-QFW Protiva - Petr (1885-1973)]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:JFB7-6NT|title=New York Passenger Arrival Lists (Ellis Island), 1892-1924|last=Protiva|first=|date=1904|website=FamilySearch|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nPetr was the younger brother of Marie.\n|\n|-\n|\n|c. 1904\n[[Baltimore]]\n|[https://www.familysearch.org/tree/person/details/L14N-Y98 Houdek - Anna (1890-1963)]\n|\n|-\n|\n|c. 1905\n|[https://www.familysearch.org/tree/person/details/LZYM-7YL Stepan - Josefa (1894-1967)]\n\nJosefa arrived with her adoptive family.\n|[[File:Josephine \u0160t\u011bp\u00e1nov\u00e1-Vlastnik-Krnak (1894-1967).png|center|thumb|141x141px|Josephine \u0160t\u011bp\u00e1nov\u00e1/Vlastnik-Krnak (1894-1967)]]\n|-\n|\n|c. 1905\n|[https://www.familysearch.org/tree/person/details/L14N-YMB Houdek - Anezka (1886-1960)]\n\nAnezka was the daughter of Anna Tichova.\n|[[File:Agnes Houdkov\u00e1-Player (1886-1960).png|center|thumb|Agnes Houdkov\u00e1-Player (1886-1960)]]\n|-\n|24 April 1906\n\n[[SS Kronprinz Wilhelm]]\n\n[[Bremen]][[File:The_SS_Kronprinz_Wilhelm_of_NDL_in_an_unknown_location.jpg|center|thumb]]\n|2 May 1906\n[[Ellis Island|New York]]\n|[https://www.familysearch.org/tree/person/details/L1KG-W2S Moutvic - Karel (1889-1961)]<ref>{{Cite