tesovec - Marie (1869-1927),] [https://www.familysearch.org/tree/person/details/L1KX-78N Barbora (1872-1957)]\n|[[File:Marie Kot\u011b\u0161ovcov\u00e1-Markvart (1869-1927).png|center|thumb|187x187px|Marie Kot\u011b\u0161ovcov\u00e1-Markvart (1869-1927)]]\n|-\n|SS Stuttgart\n\n[[Bremen]]\n|2 May 1893\nStopped at [[Ellis Island|New York]]\n\n4 May 1893\n\n[[Baltimore]]\n|[https://www.familysearch.org/tree/person/details/L1QP-8WQ Blazek - Jan (1873-)]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:J6BT-P6T|title=New York Passenger Arrival Lists (Ellis Island), 1892-1924|last=Blazek|first=|date=1893|website=FamilySearch|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n[https://www.familysearch.org/tree/person/details/LR74-QCT Sevcik - Frantisek (1873-1933)]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:2CSC-K5N|title=Maryland, Baltimore Passenger Lists, 1820-1948|last=Sevcik|first=|date=1893|website=FamilySearch|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n|\n|c. 1893\n|[https://www.familysearch.org/tree/person/details/L133-NC9 Popule - Marie (1871-1944)]\n|\n|-\n|\n|bef 1894\nBaltimore\n|[https://www.familysearch.org/tree/person/details/G73X-SW1 Troch - Jan]\n|\n|-\n|30 August 1894\nHH Meier\n\n[[Bremen]]\n|12 September 1894\n[[Baltimore]]\n|[https://www.familysearch.org/tree/person/details/L14R-ZRY Klecka - Frantisek (1873-1950)] [passport record though he's not in the ship's manifest]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:QV5Y-2L61|title=United States Passport Applications, 1795-1925|last=Klecka|first=|date=1908|website=FamilySearch|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nThe younger brother of Josef Klecka. He married Marie Slechtova of [[Mysl\u00edv|Mysliv]] in Baltimore.\n|[[File:Frank Joseph Klecka (1873-1950).png|center|thumb|Frank Joseph Kle\u010dka (1873-1950)]]\n|-\n|9 April 1896\n\nSS Willehad\n\n[[Bremen]][[File:SS Willehad.jpg|center|thumb