 (1907) LCCN2003653258.tif|center|thumb|123x123px|SS Kaiser Wilhelm II in June 1907]]<br />\n|16 May 1906\n\n[[Ellis Island|New York]]\n|[https://www.familysearch.org/tree/person/details/L2P1-LX9 Behensky - Vaclav (1891-1925)] [to meet an unidentified Anton Sevisky]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:JFCK-RZ9|title=New York Passenger Arrival Lists (Ellis Island), 1892-1924|last=Behensky|first=|date=1906|website=FamilySearch|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n[https://www.familysearch.org/tree/person/details/L133-ND9 Straka - Vojtech (1857-1913)] [with his wife from Trebomyslice, Marie Jindrova, and 5 children],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:JFCK-RML|title=New York Passenger Arrival Lists (Ellis Island), 1892-1924|last=Straka|first=|date=1906|website=FamilySearch|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> [https://www.familysearch.org/tree/person/details/L133-LYY Josef (1889-1948),] [https://www.familysearch.org/tree/person/details/L1QP-2QX Marie (1891-),] [https://www.familysearch.org/tree/person/details/L133-VJG Vojtech (1892-1953),] [https://www.familysearch.org/tree/person/details/L1QP-RLQ Josefa (1895-),] [https://www.familysearch.org/tree/person/details/L1QP-GDR Silvestr (1897-1967)]\n|[[File:James Behensk\u00fd (1891-1925).png|center|thumb|137x137px|James Behensk\u00fd (1891-1925)]][[File:Mary Anna Strakov\u00e1-Petr (1891-).png|center|thumb|Mary Anna Strakov\u00e1-Petr (1891-)]]\n|-\n|5 May 1906\n[[SS Prinzess Alice]]\n\n[[Bremen]][[File:SS Princess Alice interned at Cebu, Philippines.jpg|center|thumb]]<br />\n|17 May 1906\n[[Ellis Island|New York]]\n|[https://www.familysearch.org/tree/person/details/LRVW-HJF Paty - Frantisek (1867-1939)]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:JFCL-8JF|title=New York Passenger Arrival Lists (Ellis Island), 1892-1924|last=Paty|first=|date=1906|website=FamilySearch|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-da